The paper deals with graph embeddings on 2-dimensional surfaces, which is a topic in computational geometry (cs.CG). The paper also involves algorithms for testing if a given map of a graph can be approximated by an embedding, which falls under the category of data structures (cs.DS). The Hanani-Tutte theorem is a classical result in graph theory (cs.GT), and the paper also involves combinatorial arguments (cs.DM) and topological considerations (cs.SD) in its proof.
